<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="32" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="32">
Burdsall and Eslyn (1974) introduced 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Phanerochaete" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Phanerochaete chrysosporium" order="Polyporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="chrysosporium">Phanerochaete chrysosporium</taxonomicName>
which was collected on dead wood of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Platanaceae" genus="Platanus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Platanus wrightii" order="Proteales" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wrightii">Platanus wrightii</taxonomicName>
in the USA. Phylogenetic analysis of ITS sequence data shows this taxon groups with 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Phanerochaete" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Phanerochaete chrysosporium" order="Polyporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="chrysosporium">Phanerochaete chrysosporium</taxonomicName>
(sequences obtained from GenBank) that had been collected from different hosts. The phylogenetic placement of this species is shown in Figure 3.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
